      {
        "title": "MSI X870 exceed expectations",
        "text": "This board and the Ryzen 7 x3d deployed flawlessly for me. I'd set up a dual boot for Mint and W11. Mint struggled initially with the WiFi deployment and was resolved within a day by the Mint community. This board/processor combo is preforming beyond expectations. The build quality is excellent. Fitment in the 4000d case with an Artic 360 and the 9070xt is excellent.\n\nMy only complaint is the location of a pair of M.2 5x4 channels directly under the GPU. Servicing the drives will require the GPU to be removed or you're gonna struggle with/endanger the hardware you're working on and around.",
        "user_name": "frosty-j",
        "source": "bestbuy.ca",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "a year ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK1dxDLaRlqRSOzm4EjdN-pXgh8_JxOXZZCwuYF1UqcmB-H2uU5EfyPq9rZ82Ekhs013fg=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Best So far",
        "text": "I love this board, love the black with green. Easy to setup as well with the easy slot for the gpu. 4 nvme's are a bonus and with gen5 with speeds up to 14k what else can you possibly ask for. I put 128ddr5 6400 on mine with no issues with posting. Just remember when installing your ram that you put the first one in the correct dimm first, read the manual or dowload it from msi website. I have never had any issues with any tomahawk series. All i need now is the new 5000 series of gpu's lol.",
        "user_name": "kewtd",
        "source": "bestbuy.ca",
